data.name: RateCellType_colors_Description
data.value: The maximum configuration is three colors, representing the color at low score, the color at medium score, and the color at high score

data.name: ShowMessageBox_DialogResultDescription
data.value: Click OK to return the result as confirm, click Cancel to return the result as cancel, click Close button to return the result as close

data.name: AvatarCellType_showSystemAvatar_Description
data.value: When check 'Show System Avatar' option, AvatarCellType will use cell value as a system user name and try to get avator image of specific user. You can use UserInfoView or %CurrentUser% keyword to get user name.

data.name: Breadcrumb_defaultBehavior_Description
data.value: Default behavior is navigate the page with same name of breadcrumb part. Uncheck this option can customize the click behavior by command.

data.name: CascaderCellType_checkStrictly_Description
data.value: When this option is checked, the parent-child node association is canceled and any level option can be selected.

data.name: CascaderCellType_SetDataSourceByObjTree_Description
CascaderCellType_valueProperty_Description
data.value: When using different value property names at multiple levels, you can use the | separation, e.g. 'provinceId|cityId'

data.name: CascaderCellType_labelProperty_Description
data.value: If you do not set a label property name, the value property is considered equal, and when using different label properties at multiple levels, you can use the | Separation, e.g. 'provinceName|cityName'

data.name: CascaderCellType_childrenProperty_Description
data.value: If multiple children-attributes are different for example the children-attribute of a province is a city, you can use the "|" Separation, e.g. 'provinces|cities|streets'

data.name: CascaderCellType_SetDataSourceByIdPidTable_Description
data.value: Using a table JSON object tree as a data source for cells, the JSON format example is as follows [ {"value": 1, "label": "Department1", "parentValue": null}, {"value": 2, "label": "Department1-1", "parentValue": 1}, {"value": 3, "label": "Department1-2", "parentValue": 1}, {"value": 4, "label": "Department1-2-1", "parentValue": 3}, {"value": 5, "label": "Department2", "parentValue": null}, {"value": 6, "label": "Department3", "parentValue": null} ] The above data assumes that the 'value attribute' is value, the 'label attribute name' is label, and the 'parent value attribute name' is 'parentValue' The table format is a common multi-level data preservation format in databases

data.name: CascaderCellType_SetDataSourceByIdPidTable_labelProperty_Description
data.value: If you do not set the label property name, the value property is considered equal

data.name: InputCellType_Select_Description
data.value: Focus the input box then select all text

data.name: NavMenuCellType_GetSelectPath_Description
data.value: Select path is a array, Can use formula =TEXTJOIN("/",1,valuePath) convert array to string, or use loop command access every path part.

data.name: PaginationCellType_pagerCount_Description
data.value: Odd number greater than or equal to 5 and less than or equal to 21

data.name: ProgressCellType_textFormula_Description
data.value: Customize display text by formula, e.g. ="Totally used "&A1&"G", keep this setting empty will display as percentage like 50%

data.name: SelectCellType_reserveKeyword_Description
data.value: When multiple select and searchable, whether to retain the current search keyword after selecting an option

data.name: SelectCellType_SetDataSourceByStringArray_Description
data.value: Using a dynamic JSON string array as the data source for cells, json format example is as follows [ "Banana", "Apple", "Pear" ] Usually, the data source can be obtained from a web service through an HTTP request command, or it can be obtained through a server-side command

data.name: SelectCellType_SetDataSourceByObjArray_Description
data.value: Using a dynamic JSON object as a data source for cells, an example of JSON format is as follows [ {"value": 1, "label": "Banana"}, {"value": 2, "label": "Apple"}, {"value": 3, "label": "Pear"} ] The above data assumes that the 'value attribute' is value and the 'label attribute name' is label Typically, a JSON data source can be obtained from a web service via an HTTP request command, or from a server-side command

data.name: SelectCellType_SetDataSourceByObjArray_labelProperty_Description
data.value: If you do not set the label property name, the value property is considered equal

data.name: SliderCellType_showSteps_Desciption
data.value: Usually used in conjunction with step setting

data.name: TagCellType_ColorList_Description
data.value: The color of the tag cycles from the first color in the color list. For example, the color list has 3 items, the first three tags will use the first three colors, the fourth will use the first color, and so on. If you want all tags to be the same color, you can keep one item in the color list

data.name: TagCellType_distinct_Description
data.value: If the label text is duplicated, only the first item is displayed

data.name: ShowNotification_Duration_Description
data.value: Display time, milliseconds. Setting to 0 does not automatically close

data.name: ShowNotification_Offset_Description
data.value: At the same time, all notification box instances should have the same offset

data.name: Notification_Context_Description
data.value: Use to store the context value (such as ID) which will be used in click notification command

data.name: Timeline_bindingOptions_Columns_Description
data.value: color: node color support color names, such as "red", "black" Supports hexadecimal notation such as "#002316" Support rgb or rgba formats such as: "rgb(0,10,100)" or "rgba(0,10,100,0.5)"

data.name: Timeline_IsTimestampSort_Description
data.value: Automatic sorting based on timestamp, otherwise, use default data order

data.name: UploadCellType_tipText_DefaultValue
data.value: Only jpg/png files can be uploaded

data.name: ShowMessage_Duration_Description
data.value: Automatically shut down duration. Setting to 0 does not automatically shut down

data.name: ShowMessage_Offset_Description
data.value: The offset of the message box from the top of the window

data.name: ShowMessage_DistinguishCancelAndClose_Description
data.value: Cancel (click the Cancel button) Close (click the Close button or mask layer, press ESC)

data.name: DefaultTreeSource
UploadCellType_OverFileCountLimitError
data.value: The file count limit is ${limit}, This time choosed file count is ${length} ,totally ${total}

data.name: UploadCellType_OverFileSizeLimitError
data.value: The size of the uploaded file exceeds the limit

data.name: ProgressCellType_SetBackgroundColor_Description
data.value: Setting the background color will set the status to empty.

data.name: Timeline_SetDataSource_Description
data.value: Using a dynamic JSON object as a data source for cells, an example of JSON format is as follows [ {"content": "Activity start", "timestamp": "2018-04-15"}, {"content": "Approved", "timestamp": "2018-04-13"}, {"content": "Create Success", "timestamp": "2018-04-11"} ] The above data assumes that the 'content attribute' is content and the 'timestamp attribute name' is timestamp Typically, a JSON data source can be obtained from a web service via an HTTP request command, or from a server-side command

data.name: MethodName_ReloadBindingItems_Description
data.value: If the binding is changed but the binding items can't reload data automatically, use this operation can force reload binding items

data.name: HideItemsParam_ItemsDescription
data.value: Multiple menu items can be separated by English commas. Such as Menu1,Menu2.

data.name: TabHeader_HideItemsParam_ItemsDescription
data.value: Multiple menu items can be separated by English commas. Such as Tab1,Tab2.
